    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect protocol state machine transition in LDPC decoder capability check\n\n### Summary\nThere is an incorrect protocol state machine transition that violates 3GPP specification downstream of function check_required_dev_capabilities in openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_coding/nrLDPC_coding_aal/nrLDPC_coding_aal.c. When calling check_required_dev_capabilities() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in check_required_dev_capabilities or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure system with LDPC-capable device that doesn't support RTE_BBDEV_LDPC_ITERATION_STOP_ENABLE flag\n2. Attempt to initialize LDPC decoder offload functionality\n3. Observe that device is incorrectly rejected despite being 3GPP compliant\n4. System fails to utilize available hardware acceleration\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_decoder/nrLDPC_decoder_offload.c`: Modified `check_dev_cap()` function to remove overly restrictive capability checking that was rejecting compliant devices\n"
}